loud gpu based jobs india as per naukari/linkedin
In India, cloud GPU-based roles are primarily concentrated in Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Pune, and Delhi-NCR. These jobs are heavily tied to the rapid growth of the Global Capability Center (GCC) ecosystem and the domestic push for AI-native infrastructure. 

1. Top Companies Hiring (Naukri & LinkedIn)
Based on current active listings, the following companies are leading the demand for GPU-related talent in India:
Infrastructure & Chipmakers: NVIDIA (leading with hundreds of roles), AMD, Intel, Qualcomm, and MediaTek.
Cloud & Tech Giants: Microsoft (Azure AI infrastructure), Google (Google Cloud & AI), Meta (Accelerator systems), and Oracle.
Emerging AI Startups: Neysa (Indian AI cloud startup), Pocket FM (Video Generation research), and CynLr (Robotics).
Consulting & Services: KPMG India, HCLTech, Infosys, and L&T. 

2. Key Job Roles & Specializations
The demand has shifted from general cloud management to specialized GPU infrastructure roles:
ML Infrastructure Engineer: Focusing on building GPU clusters and distributed training systems.
Accelerated Compute Engineer: Managing NVIDIA vGPU, MIG, and high-performance networking like InfiniBand.
GPU Architect/Performance Engineer: Profiling and optimizing power/performance at the hardware and driver levels.
LLMOps/Generative AI Engineer: Deploying and serving Large Language Models on cloud GPU resources. 

3. Salary & Market Trends (2025-2026)
The market shows a significant premium for candidates who combine cloud and GPU-specific skills:
Experience Premiums: Roles with AI/ML cloud skills can command a 30% to 45% premium over standard cloud engineering salaries.
Entry-Level Growth: Freshers in cloud/DevOps tracks typically start at ₹4–₹6.5 LPA, while mid-level engineers (3–7 years) earn between ₹8–₹20 LPA.
Market Outlook: India's semiconductor and AI infrastructure sector is expected to create one million jobs by 2026 as data center capacity doubles. 

4. Required Tech Stack
To land these roles, recruiters on LinkedIn and Naukri prioritize:
Languages: C++, Python, and CUDA.
Infrastructure: Kubernetes (GPU-aware scheduling), Docker, and Terraform.
GPU Tools: NVIDIA vGPU, MIG, TensorRT, and DeepStream. 

These job listings from LinkedIn and Naukri detail cloud GPU roles in India, including specific companies, required skills, and salary expectations.
